Text.SourceString: Oh, hey! It’s nice to see you again.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, hey! It’s nice to see you again.

Text.SourceString: It’ll be nice to have more farmers here.//Being able to get local produce will be a game changer.
Text.LocalizedString: It’ll be nice to have more farmers here.//Being able to get local produce will be a game changer.

Text.SourceString: I went for a run in the forest this morning and made it back before <NPCName>Valentina</> had to leave for school. It's such a great way to kickstart the day!
Text.LocalizedString: I went for a run in the forest this morning and made it back before <NPCName>Valentina</> had to leave for school. It's such a great way to kickstart the day!

Text.SourceString: Hmm? Oh yeah, it's kinda like a wake-up call.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm? Oh yeah, it's kinda like a wake-up call.

Text.SourceString: It's kinda sad to think about, but if I don't take <NPCName>Valentina</> to school now, when else would I get to do it?
Text.LocalizedString: It's kinda sad to think about, but if I don't take <NPCName>Valentina</> to school now, when else would I get to do it?

Text.SourceString: She'll be all grown up and off to university before we know it.//<portrait=annoyed>Time really does fly, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: She'll be all grown up and off to university before we know it.//<portrait=annoyed>Time really does fly, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: My sis, <NPCName>Alice</>, is so soft-spoken. Sometimes I can barely hear what she's saying.
Text.LocalizedString: My sis, <NPCName>Alice</>, is so soft-spoken. Sometimes I can barely hear what she's saying.

Text.SourceString: That girl needs to turn it up a notch.//Speak up more!
Text.LocalizedString: That girl needs to turn it up a notch.//Speak up more!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Alice</> and I are twins, but no, I can't read her mind.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Alice</> and I are twins, but no, I can't read her mind.

Text.SourceString: She can't even feel it when I give her a little pinch.//And no, we don't do everything together.
Text.LocalizedString: She can't even feel it when I give her a little pinch.//And no, we don't do everything together.

Text.SourceString: I try my best to take <NPCName>Valentina</> to school every morning. It's our little routine.//And on the way back, I usually grab some stuff for the inn.
Text.LocalizedString: I try my best to take <NPCName>Valentina</> to school every morning. It's our little routine.//And on the way back, I usually grab some stuff for the inn.

Text.SourceString: I let <NPCName>Alice</> handle our wine selection.//Honestly, I'm not too concerned about alcohol.
Text.LocalizedString: I let <NPCName>Alice</> handle our wine selection.//Honestly, I'm not too concerned about alcohol.

Text.SourceString: We usually get our wine from Hillside Vineyard, and their business seems to be doing well, so whatever they're making must be good.
Text.LocalizedString: We usually get our wine from Hillside Vineyard, and their business seems to be doing well, so whatever they're making must be good.

Text.SourceString: My sister may look small, but gosh, can she eat!//<portrait=happy>Especially when she makes minced jackfruit pie.//<portrait=normal>A healthy appetite is good!
Text.LocalizedString: My sister may look small, but gosh, can she eat!//<portrait=happy>Especially when she makes minced jackfruit pie.//<portrait=normal>A healthy appetite is good!

Text.SourceString: It’s one of her favorite dishes, by the way.//That and green smoothies… Same as me!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s one of her favorite dishes, by the way.//That and green smoothies… Same as me!

Text.SourceString: Have you ever tried making eggplant lasagna? It's yummy, and it's super easy to make.//Oh, but you'll need a ceramic bowl for that.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you ever tried making eggplant lasagna? It's yummy, and it's super easy to make.//Oh, but you'll need a ceramic bowl for that.

Text.SourceString: I make it all the time. I practically know the recipe by heart.
Text.LocalizedString: I make it all the time. I practically know the recipe by heart.

Text.SourceString: The inn is doing alright, but it's not exactly bursting at the seams. Well, not as much as I'd love it to be!//<portrait=happy>But we do have a handful of regular customers.
Text.LocalizedString: The inn is doing alright, but it's not exactly bursting at the seams. Well, not as much as I'd love it to be!//<portrait=happy>But we do have a handful of regular customers.

Text.SourceString: Oh, that's right! You probably know them, huh?//<NPCName>Eva</> and <NPCName>Macy</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, that's right! You probably know them, huh?//<NPCName>Eva</> and <NPCName>Macy</>?

Text.SourceString: It’s Friday again. No school for the kids tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s Friday again. No school for the kids tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: Gotta make sure <NPCName>Valentina</> gets her weekend reading done.//<portrait=normal>Sometimes she gets so caught up in things and forgets about it.
Text.LocalizedString: Gotta make sure <NPCName>Valentina</> gets her weekend reading done.//<portrait=normal>Sometimes she gets so caught up in things and forgets about it.

Text.SourceString: Does the air feel a bit musty to you? I'm worried there might be some mold lurking around the inn.
Text.LocalizedString: Does the air feel a bit musty to you? I'm worried there might be some mold lurking around the inn.

Text.SourceString: We get tons of tourists who come here specifically for the festivals.
Text.LocalizedString: We get tons of tourists who come here specifically for the festivals.

Text.SourceString: We're kind of a big deal, you know.
Text.LocalizedString: We're kind of a big deal, you know.

Text.SourceString: I set up my old sewing machine for the guests to use.//It's never too late to learn a new skill.
Text.LocalizedString: I set up my old sewing machine for the guests to use.//It's never too late to learn a new skill.

Text.SourceString: Let me tell you something about my sister. <NPCName>Alice</> took a neuroscience class on zombies, and they did a behavioral study to compare zombie brains to human brains.
Text.LocalizedString: Let me tell you something about my sister. <NPCName>Alice</> took a neuroscience class on zombies, and they did a behavioral study to compare zombie brains to human brains.

Text.SourceString: Of course not. Zombies aren’t real. Don’t be silly!
Text.LocalizedString: Of course not. Zombies aren’t real. Don’t be silly!

Text.SourceString: And get this, yeah? <NPCName>Alice</> also took an astrobiology class on the search for extraterrestrial life. I don’t know what she was thinking…
Text.LocalizedString: And get this, yeah? <NPCName>Alice</> also took an astrobiology class on the search for extraterrestrial life. I don’t know what she was thinking…

Text.SourceString: Don’t know if you know this. But I used to be fun, <PlayerName>$player</>. Now I get excited about a trip to the grocery store.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t know if you know this. But I used to be fun, <PlayerName>$player</>. Now I get excited about a trip to the grocery store.

Text.SourceString: Gotta embrace the new me, I guess.
Text.LocalizedString: Gotta embrace the new me, I guess.

Text.SourceString: So, what's on your agenda for the week? Anything exciting?
Text.LocalizedString: So, what's on your agenda for the week? Anything exciting?

Text.SourceString: I don't talk about it much, but having a child really flipped my life around.//It changed me in so many ways...
Text.LocalizedString: I don't talk about it much, but having a child really flipped my life around.//It changed me in so many ways...

Text.SourceString: Oh, in a good way, of course. Being a parent brings a whole new sense of purpose into your life.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, in a good way, of course. Being a parent brings a whole new sense of purpose into your life.

Text.SourceString: I never cared about my diet or lifestyle until I had <NPCName>Valentina</>. Then I became a label-reading momster. Ha!
Text.LocalizedString: I never cared about my diet or lifestyle until I had <NPCName>Valentina</>. Then I became a label-reading momster. Ha!

Text.SourceString: Not even going to deny it. That's who I am now.
Text.LocalizedString: Not even going to deny it. That's who I am now.

Text.SourceString: My ex’s cousin <NPCName>Rafael</> helps out with odd jobs around the inn when he comes to visit <NPCName>Valentina</> on Sundays.
Text.LocalizedString: My ex’s cousin <NPCName>Rafael</> helps out with odd jobs around the inn when he comes to visit <NPCName>Valentina</> on Sundays.

Text.SourceString: You know him, don’t you? Yeah, he’s pretty helpful.
Text.LocalizedString: You know him, don’t you? Yeah, he’s pretty helpful.

Text.SourceString: Got a lot of cleaning up to do today...
Text.LocalizedString: Got a lot of cleaning up to do today...

Text.SourceString: Well, that’s what weekends are for. Might as well roll up my sleeves and get to work.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, that’s what weekends are for. Might as well roll up my sleeves and get to work.

Text.SourceString: I had <NPCName>Valentina</> when I was pretty young. But I want to be there for her for as long as possible.
Text.LocalizedString: I had <NPCName>Valentina</> when I was pretty young. But I want to be there for her for as long as possible.

Text.SourceString: That's why I'm being more mindful of what I eat. No more junk food for me!
Text.LocalizedString: That's why I'm being more mindful of what I eat. No more junk food for me!

Text.SourceString: I stay pretty active, but I just can't get into the activities my ex loves.
Text.LocalizedString: I stay pretty active, but I just can't get into the activities my ex loves.

Text.SourceString: Rock climbing? Diving? Nah, not my cup of tea.
Text.LocalizedString: Rock climbing? Diving? Nah, not my cup of tea.

Text.SourceString: Are you ready for Spring cleaning, <PlayerName>$player</>? I know I am. I’ve prepared for this all year.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you ready for Spring cleaning, <PlayerName>$player</>? I know I am. I’ve prepared for this all year.

Text.SourceString: Oh, aren’t you glad Winter is over? I certainly am. Besides the snow, the cold was unbearable.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, aren’t you glad Winter is over? I certainly am. Besides the snow, the cold was unbearable.

Text.SourceString: The inn is so big… It’s not easy to clean it alone.//I don’t mind, though. I even make my own cleaning solution.
Text.LocalizedString: The inn is so big… It’s not easy to clean it alone.//I don’t mind, though. I even make my own cleaning solution.

Text.SourceString: *singing* Clean, clean, clean~
Text.LocalizedString: *singing* Clean, clean, clean~

Text.SourceString: I'm so glad I don't have to run in the cold anymore!//The great thing about running is that once you warm up, you don't feel the cold anymore. But getting started can be tough.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm so glad I don't have to run in the cold anymore!//The great thing about running is that once you warm up, you don't feel the cold anymore. But getting started can be tough.

Text.SourceString: I love running in Spring.//<portrait=normal>It’s so nice to hear all the animals again and see all the plants blooming.//<portrait=happy>It gives me more energy to run!
Text.LocalizedString: I love running in Spring.//<portrait=normal>It’s so nice to hear all the animals again and see all the plants blooming.//<portrait=happy>It gives me more energy to run!

Text.SourceString: Now that Winter is over, it's time to wash all the blankets and put them in storage.
Text.LocalizedString: Now that Winter is over, it's time to wash all the blankets and put them in storage.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Valentina’s</> birthday is coming up soon. It’s on the 3rd of Summer.//<portrait=annoyed>Should I throw a big birthday party at the inn or just have a picnic at the beach?
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Valentina’s</> birthday is coming up soon. It’s on the 3rd of Summer.//<portrait=annoyed>Should I throw a big birthday party at the inn or just have a picnic at the beach?

Text.SourceString: Phew, I've cleaned everything on my list right on schedule!
Text.LocalizedString: Phew, I've cleaned everything on my list right on schedule!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Valentina</> gets really active in Summer. I think she’s excited to go out and play with her dad.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Valentina</> gets really active in Summer. I think she’s excited to go out and play with her dad.

Text.SourceString: Living by the beach, it gets pretty hot and humid. Layering up is not an option for me.
Text.LocalizedString: Living by the beach, it gets pretty hot and humid. Layering up is not an option for me.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice to see people getting together and cleaning up the beach.//It's one of my favorite things about Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice to see people getting together and cleaning up the beach.//It's one of my favorite things about Summer.

Text.SourceString: I made some homemade bug repellent, but it doesn't seem to be doing the trick.//Or maybe these Summer bugs are just super resilient...
Text.LocalizedString: I made some homemade bug repellent, but it doesn't seem to be doing the trick.//Or maybe these Summer bugs are just super resilient...

Text.SourceString: I've put out my homemade bug repellent in the lobby.//It's free for everyone to use, and guests can take a mini bottle with them if they want.
Text.LocalizedString: I've put out my homemade bug repellent in the lobby.//It's free for everyone to use, and guests can take a mini bottle with them if they want.

Text.SourceString: Lemongrass is the main ingredient in my bug repellent… It smells really strong.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t hate it… It’s just… No point using perfume, you know? It would just be overpowered.
Text.LocalizedString: Lemongrass is the main ingredient in my bug repellent… It smells really strong.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t hate it… It’s just… No point using perfume, you know? It would just be overpowered.

Text.SourceString: Oh, I better make some minced jackfruit pies for dinner with some fresh jackfruit. It’s in season now!//Sounds so yum!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, I better make some minced jackfruit pies for dinner with some fresh jackfruit. It’s in season now!//Sounds so yum!

Text.SourceString: I’m a little sad Spring is over, but Summer isn’t so bad.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m a little sad Spring is over, but Summer isn’t so bad.

Text.SourceString: I wonder if it's worth turning on the sprinklers to keep the grass green, or if it'll just be a waste of water.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if it's worth turning on the sprinklers to keep the grass green, or if it'll just be a waste of water.

Text.SourceString: Some of the guests complained about the yellow grass… No, no, not recently. It was a few years ago.//I told them it’s just the way the grass is here, but they wouldn’t accept it.
Text.LocalizedString: Some of the guests complained about the yellow grass… No, no, not recently. It was a few years ago.//I told them it’s just the way the grass is here, but they wouldn’t accept it.

Text.SourceString: We’re bracing ourselves for the oncoming Winter. You should, too.//Heater, blankets… What else do I need?
Text.LocalizedString: We’re bracing ourselves for the oncoming Winter. You should, too.//Heater, blankets… What else do I need?

Text.SourceString: Fall is such a beautiful season, don't you think?
Text.LocalizedString: Fall is such a beautiful season, don't you think?

Text.SourceString: I enjoy running in Fall.//<portrait=blushing>It's cool enough that I don't overheat, but not too cold that I feel like my toes are freezing off.
Text.LocalizedString: I enjoy running in Fall.//<portrait=blushing>It's cool enough that I don't overheat, but not too cold that I feel like my toes are freezing off.

Text.SourceString: We usually get more guests the closer we get to the Harvest Festival.//<portrait=concerned>Some of them are up from Beluga Bay for the harvest display, and the rest are just tourists who are curious about the festival.
Text.LocalizedString: We usually get more guests the closer we get to the Harvest Festival.//<portrait=concerned>Some of them are up from Beluga Bay for the harvest display, and the rest are just tourists who are curious about the festival.

Text.SourceString: I have to make sure the heaters are working properly before Winter starts… <Italic>Oh!</> And see that we have enough blankets for everyone.//<portrait=annoyed>I asked <NPCName>Alice</> to take care of the blankets a few years ago, but she missed some of the rooms, so I’m taking care of them now.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to make sure the heaters are working properly before Winter starts… <Italic>Oh!</> And see that we have enough blankets for everyone.//<portrait=annoyed>I asked <NPCName>Alice</> to take care of the blankets a few years ago, but she missed some of the rooms, so I’m taking care of them now.

Text.SourceString: I have to get the blanket boxes from storage.//I’m gonna ask <NPCName>Rafael</> to do it next weekend… And I have to check the battery in the carbon monoxide detector.//I do it every year at the very least!
Text.LocalizedString: I have to get the blanket boxes from storage.//I’m gonna ask <NPCName>Rafael</> to do it next weekend… And I have to check the battery in the carbon monoxide detector.//I do it every year at the very least!

Text.SourceString: You can run for longer in cooler weather. It's easier to catch your breath.//<portrait=annoyed>Well, for me at least, not sure about you.
Text.LocalizedString: You can run for longer in cooler weather. It's easier to catch your breath.//<portrait=annoyed>Well, for me at least, not sure about you.

Text.SourceString: Oh, here we go. It’s Winter again…
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, here we go. It’s Winter again…

Text.SourceString: Good news! We have enough blankets for the guests…I think.//Let’s hope!
Text.LocalizedString: Good news! We have enough blankets for the guests…I think.//Let’s hope!

Text.SourceString: I know it’s my birthday month, but honestly, I don’t really care about birthdays… The best thing about mine is <NPCName>Alice</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I know it’s my birthday month, but honestly, I don’t really care about birthdays… The best thing about mine is <NPCName>Alice</>.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Valentina</> can be <Italic>very</> excessive when it comes to accessorizing her snowmen. She sneaks and takes my robe, my hat…//Some of the things she takes are Wabanana, you know…
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Valentina</> can be <Italic>very</> excessive when it comes to accessorizing her snowmen. She sneaks and takes my robe, my hat…//Some of the things she takes are Wabanana, you know…

Text.SourceString: Ugh, I don’t want to give up my morning runs, but I’m seriously considering it.//<portrait=concerned>It’s so cold!
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh, I don’t want to give up my morning runs, but I’m seriously considering it.//<portrait=concerned>It’s so cold!

Text.SourceString: Our birthday is coming up soon. What should I do for <NPCName>Alice</>? Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: Our birthday is coming up soon. What should I do for <NPCName>Alice</>? Hmm…

Text.SourceString: It's always mind-blowing to think that I have a twin.
Text.LocalizedString: It's always mind-blowing to think that I have a twin.

Text.SourceString: I’m looking forward to Spring.//Making my cleaning solution tonight… Getting ready for Spring cleaning. Woo-hoo!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m looking forward to Spring.//Making my cleaning solution tonight… Getting ready for Spring cleaning. Woo-hoo!

Text.SourceString: Phew! Quite the party last night, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Phew! Quite the party last night, huh?

Text.SourceString: don't think I got enough sleep... I still feel so tired.
Text.LocalizedString: don't think I got enough sleep... I still feel so tired.

Text.SourceString: It’s <NpcName>Joko’s</> birthday tomorrow… Hmm…//<portrait=normal>Do you think I should get him some pineapples? Or a jar of yogurt?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s <NpcName>Joko’s</> birthday tomorrow… Hmm…//<portrait=normal>Do you think I should get him some pineapples? Or a jar of yogurt?

Text.SourceString: Yeah, I think he would appreciate it.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, I think he would appreciate it.

Text.SourceString: Okay. It’s a healthy snack.
Text.LocalizedString: Okay. It’s a healthy snack.

Special.SourceString: Eww, not pineapples. A jar of yogurt, of course.
Special.LocalizedString: Eww, not pineapples. A jar of yogurt, of course.

82.SpecialTag: Eww, not pineapples. A jar of yogurt, of course.
82.Question: R2

Text.SourceString: I expected to see more rain than this.
Text.LocalizedString: I expected to see more rain than this.

Text.SourceString: You know, I have to say… Quite a name you’ve got, <PlayerName>$player</>.//Is there a meaning behind it?
Text.LocalizedString: You know, I have to say… Quite a name you’ve got, <PlayerName>$player</>.//Is there a meaning behind it?

Text.SourceString: My parents never explained why they named me <NPCName>Suki</> and my sister <NPCName>Alice</>…
Text.LocalizedString: My parents never explained why they named me <NPCName>Suki</> and my sister <NPCName>Alice</>…

Text.SourceString: I ate so much yesterday at the Cherry Blossom Festival.//I think I’m still full today. *laughs*
Text.LocalizedString: I ate so much yesterday at the Cherry Blossom Festival.//I think I’m still full today. *laughs*

Text.SourceString: The beach cleanup is an awesome thing, but we also need to remember to use less plastic and recycle.
Text.LocalizedString: The beach cleanup is an awesome thing, but we also need to remember to use less plastic and recycle.

Text.SourceString: I get fresh flowers for the inn from <NPCName>Ben</>.//He gives us a discount for buying in bulk.
Text.LocalizedString: I get fresh flowers for the inn from <NPCName>Ben</>.//He gives us a discount for buying in bulk.

Text.SourceString: We get things from <NPCName>Sam’s</> store too, of course…//<portrait=happy>Um… You know, bread and things like that.
Text.LocalizedString: We get things from <NPCName>Sam’s</> store too, of course…//<portrait=happy>Um… You know, bread and things like that.

Text.SourceString: I'm just here to pick up some fresh irises for the inn.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm just here to pick up some fresh irises for the inn.

Text.SourceString: The sun is strong today... Make sure to stay hydrated, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: The sun is strong today... Make sure to stay hydrated, okay?

Text.SourceString: A lot of people here are so dedicated to this island.//It was amazing to see everyone together yesterday.
Text.LocalizedString: A lot of people here are so dedicated to this island.//It was amazing to see everyone together yesterday.

Text.SourceString: The nights are starting to get chilly.
Text.LocalizedString: The nights are starting to get chilly.

Text.SourceString: Make sure to bring your best produce to the Harvest Festival on the 15th.
Text.LocalizedString: Make sure to bring your best produce to the Harvest Festival on the 15th.

Text.SourceString: I thought it started to snow last night, but no. *sighs*
Text.LocalizedString: I thought it started to snow last night, but no. *sighs*

Text.SourceString: I was so excited.
Text.LocalizedString: I was so excited.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Alice</> and I grew up here. But I suppose you already knew that. I remember playing around town when I was <NPCName>Valentina’s</> age. Building rows of snowmen.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Alice</> and I grew up here. But I suppose you already knew that. I remember playing around town when I was <NPCName>Valentina’s</> age. Building rows of snowmen.

Text.SourceString: Such great memories all around.
Text.LocalizedString: Such great memories all around.

Text.SourceString: Did you know animals can have a positive effect on our mental health?//<portrait=concerned>I've tried having pets, but they don't seem to like the inn much.
Text.LocalizedString: Did you know animals can have a positive effect on our mental health?//<portrait=concerned>I've tried having pets, but they don't seem to like the inn much.

Text.SourceString: Are you going to <NPCName>Bree’s</> dinner party on the 28th? I can't decide if I should bring wine or something else.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you going to <NPCName>Bree’s</> dinner party on the 28th? I can't decide if I should bring wine or something else.

Text.SourceString: I’m not too worried about <NPCName>Valentina</>.//She knows to be careful when the ground is slippery.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not too worried about <NPCName>Valentina</>.//She knows to be careful when the ground is slippery.

Text.SourceString: Her father takes her climbing all the time, and she's good at it.
Text.LocalizedString: Her father takes her climbing all the time, and she's good at it.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Valentina</> always gives me a hard time at bedtime...//Whenever I complain to her father about it, he just says she doesn't do it at his place.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Valentina</> always gives me a hard time at bedtime...//Whenever I complain to her father about it, he just says she doesn't do it at his place.

Text.SourceString: Ugh... Of course she doesn't do it with him. I don't even want to know what time he puts her to bed.//<portrait=annoyed>I’m sure that’s why she doesn’t give him trouble.//<portrait=concerned>Midnight bedtime, for crying out loud!
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh... Of course she doesn't do it with him. I don't even want to know what time he puts her to bed.//<portrait=annoyed>I’m sure that’s why she doesn’t give him trouble.//<portrait=concerned>Midnight bedtime, for crying out loud!

Text.SourceString: It gets a bit cold in here, yeah?
Text.LocalizedString: It gets a bit cold in here, yeah?

Text.SourceString: Careful on your way home, okay, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Careful on your way home, okay, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Take Garden Lane tonight, will you?//It might be safer than going through the lookout.
Text.LocalizedString: Take Garden Lane tonight, will you?//It might be safer than going through the lookout.

Text.SourceString: Well, I just thought it might be more slippery.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, I just thought it might be more slippery.

Text.SourceString: We need to find out how to crank up the heat in here.
Text.LocalizedString: We need to find out how to crank up the heat in here.

Text.SourceString: The snow is piling up outside.
Text.LocalizedString: The snow is piling up outside.

Text.SourceString: Winter isn’t my favorite season, but days like these may make me reconsider.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter isn’t my favorite season, but days like these may make me reconsider.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Alice</> and I grew up here. But I guess you already knew that. I remember playing around the town when I was <NPCName>Valentina’s</> age… Building rows of snowmen.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Alice</> and I grew up here. But I guess you already knew that. I remember playing around the town when I was <NPCName>Valentina’s</> age… Building rows of snowmen.

Text.SourceString: Great memories all around.
Text.LocalizedString: Great memories all around.

Text.SourceString: *singing* Dum dum dum…~ <Italic>Dum!</>~
Text.LocalizedString: *singing* Dum dum dum…~ <Italic>Dum!</>~

Text.SourceString: [<NPCName>Suki</> is singing. She doesn’t sound bad.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NPCName>Suki</> is singing. She doesn’t sound bad.]

Text.SourceString: Oh, here, let me show you how to make a green smoothie.//It’s delicious, and it’s a power drink too.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, here, let me show you how to make a green smoothie.//It’s delicious, and it’s a power drink too.

Text.SourceString: It's a bit stuffy in here. We should open more windows...
Text.LocalizedString: It's a bit stuffy in here. We should open more windows...

Text.SourceString: You should take a break from farm life and stay here for a weekend or something.
Text.LocalizedString: You should take a break from farm life and stay here for a weekend or something.

Text.SourceString: You can just relax and read a book in your room with the windows open.//<portrait=happy>Fall asleep to the calming sound of the waves…
Text.LocalizedString: You can just relax and read a book in your room with the windows open.//<portrait=happy>Fall asleep to the calming sound of the waves…

Text.SourceString: We’ll give you the local discount! Heh heh.
Text.LocalizedString: We’ll give you the local discount! Heh heh.

Text.SourceString: We have plenty of books in our library.//If you don't mind well-read books, please help yourself.
Text.LocalizedString: We have plenty of books in our library.//If you don't mind well-read books, please help yourself.

Text.SourceString: Guests are welcome to take a book to read and leave one in exchange when they're done.
Text.LocalizedString: Guests are welcome to take a book to read and leave one in exchange when they're done.

Text.SourceString: It’s a “take a book, leave a book” type system…//But if someone doesn't have a book to donate, that's okay. They don't have to leave anything.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a “take a book, leave a book” type system…//But if someone doesn't have a book to donate, that's okay. They don't have to leave anything.

Text.SourceString: You should check out the pier. There are usually lots of seals hanging out there at this time.
Text.LocalizedString: You should check out the pier. There are usually lots of seals hanging out there at this time.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Valentina</> needs to clean up her room, or she won't be allowed to go to the beach tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Valentina</> needs to clean up her room, or she won't be allowed to go to the beach tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: That girl... When it's time to surf or play with her friends, she's out the door in seconds.//But when it comes to cleaning up her room... Oh gosh!
Text.LocalizedString: That girl... When it's time to surf or play with her friends, she's out the door in seconds.//But when it comes to cleaning up her room... Oh gosh!

Text.SourceString: What brings you here so early in the morning?
Text.LocalizedString: What brings you here so early in the morning?

Text.SourceString: Going fishing, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Going fishing, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: I should pick up some books and brochures for the inn while I’m here.
Text.LocalizedString: I should pick up some books and brochures for the inn while I’m here.

Text.SourceString: But I haven’t returned the books we borrowed last week.//<portrait=annoyed>I wonder if <NPCName>Millie</> will make a big deal out of it.
Text.LocalizedString: But I haven’t returned the books we borrowed last week.//<portrait=annoyed>I wonder if <NPCName>Millie</> will make a big deal out of it.

Text.SourceString: I’m here to pick up some fresh fruit and veggies for dinner. You?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m here to pick up some fresh fruit and veggies for dinner. You?

Text.SourceString: Flowers are a little expensive here. So I usually get them from <NPCName>Ben</> instead.//Besides, I sometimes buy out-of-season flowers that <NPCName>Sam</> doesn’t carry.
Text.LocalizedString: Flowers are a little expensive here. So I usually get them from <NPCName>Ben</> instead.//Besides, I sometimes buy out-of-season flowers that <NPCName>Sam</> doesn’t carry.

Text.SourceString: Sorry, <NPCName>Sam</>!
Text.LocalizedString: Sorry, <NPCName>Sam</>!

Text.SourceString: I’m feeling good today. I’m bringing my A game. *laughs*
Text.LocalizedString: I’m feeling good today. I’m bringing my A game. *laughs*

Text.SourceString: Come here to play?
Text.LocalizedString: Come here to play?

Text.SourceString: I think the mini golf course Pufferfish built is a great addition to our town.
Text.LocalizedString: I think the mini golf course Pufferfish built is a great addition to our town.

Text.SourceString: I feel bad for saying it, but I like mini golf.//It does feel like a betrayal to be enjoying it, though… I don’t know what to tell ya.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel bad for saying it, but I like mini golf.//It does feel like a betrayal to be enjoying it, though… I don’t know what to tell ya.

Text.SourceString: She and I grew up together here…//<portrait=happy>Oh! <NPCName>Nina</>… I was talking about <NPCName>Nina</>.
Text.LocalizedString: She and I grew up together here…//<portrait=happy>Oh! <NPCName>Nina</>… I was talking about <NPCName>Nina</>.

Text.SourceString: Thank you for this! It will make a very fresh green smoothie. I’ll send you the recipe tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: Thank you for this! It will make a very fresh green smoothie. I’ll send you the recipe tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: So, how much do I owe you?
Text.LocalizedString: So, how much do I owe you?

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Valentina</> keeps asking if she can go to the forest by herself.//<portrait=annoyed>I just don’t think it’s safe.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Valentina</> keeps asking if she can go to the forest by herself.//<portrait=annoyed>I just don’t think it’s safe.

Text.SourceString: I’m not worried about people, really… You never know what else lives there.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t actually believe it… But nothing’s wrong with being careful, I think.//<portrait=annoyed>Hmm… <NPCName>Alice</>has gotten her outrageous theories into my head.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not worried about people, really… You never know what else lives there.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t actually believe it… But nothing’s wrong with being careful, I think.//<portrait=annoyed>Hmm… <NPCName>Alice</>has gotten her outrageous theories into my head.

Text.SourceString: <Italic>Finding Love from Within</> is my absolute favorite book.//It gives you insights into so many things. I always feel like I'm moving forward when I read it.
Text.LocalizedString: <Italic>Finding Love from Within</> is my absolute favorite book.//It gives you insights into so many things. I always feel like I'm moving forward when I read it.

Text.SourceString: I read both Rachel Abram's and Tyna Smith's <Italic>Finding Love from Within</>. They're completely different books.//I personally prefer Rachel Abram's version much better.
Text.LocalizedString: I read both Rachel Abram's and Tyna Smith's <Italic>Finding Love from Within</>. They're completely different books.//I personally prefer Rachel Abram's version much better.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Rafael</> and <NPCName>Pablo</> come to the inn a lot.//<portrait=happy>They’re great uncles to Valentina. Their whole family is very affectionate… Lovey-dovey, you know?//<portrait=normal>I’m grateful <NPCName>Valentina</> was born into their family.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Rafael</> and <NPCName>Pablo</> come to the inn a lot.//<portrait=happy>They’re great uncles to Valentina. Their whole family is very affectionate… Lovey-dovey, you know?//<portrait=normal>I’m grateful <NPCName>Valentina</> was born into their family.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Rafael</> or <NPCName>Pablo</>? What?! Neither of them is my ex.//<portrait=happy>My ex-husband is <NPCName>Antonio</>… He's one of their cousins.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Rafael</> or <NPCName>Pablo</>? What?! Neither of them is my ex.//<portrait=happy>My ex-husband is <NPCName>Antonio</>… He's one of their cousins.

Text.SourceString: Oh my! <PlayerName>$player</>, what day is it?//<portrait=normal>Tuesday? Thank goodness. I thought I missed a day in my cardio routine.//It’s okay. I’m okay!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh my! <PlayerName>$player</>, what day is it?//<portrait=normal>Tuesday? Thank goodness. I thought I missed a day in my cardio routine.//It’s okay. I’m okay!

Text.SourceString: According to this book I'm reading, we should all be more grateful. Supposedly, it leads to a 15 percent increase in happiness within two weeks.//<portrait=happy>I’m giving it a try. I mean, why not?
Text.LocalizedString: According to this book I'm reading, we should all be more grateful. Supposedly, it leads to a 15 percent increase in happiness within two weeks.//<portrait=happy>I’m giving it a try. I mean, why not?

Text.SourceString: I’ve been keeping a gratitude journal for a week.//In just seven more days, I’ll be a new, happier me!
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been keeping a gratitude journal for a week.//In just seven more days, I’ll be a new, happier me!

Text.SourceString: You meet a lot of people working at an inn.//Traveling does that too.
Text.LocalizedString: You meet a lot of people working at an inn.//Traveling does that too.

Text.SourceString: The inn is a great place to live. It may not be a conventional place to grow up, with strangers under the same roof and all. //But <NPCName>Alice</> and I grew up there, and we had a lot of fun.//<portrait=happy>I think <NPCName>Valentina</> will do just fine.
Text.LocalizedString: The inn is a great place to live. It may not be a conventional place to grow up, with strangers under the same roof and all. //But <NPCName>Alice</> and I grew up there, and we had a lot of fun.//<portrait=happy>I think <NPCName>Valentina</> will do just fine.

Text.SourceString: I like to change up my exercise routine every week so I don't get bored.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to change up my exercise routine every week so I don't get bored.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Valentina</> is the same way. She gets bored easily.//<portrait=normal>Thankfully, her dad keeps her active with things like basketball and rock climbing.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Valentina</> is the same way. She gets bored easily.//<portrait=normal>Thankfully, her dad keeps her active with things like basketball and rock climbing.

Text.SourceString: If you ever need a place to stay, you're welcome at the inn.
Text.LocalizedString: If you ever need a place to stay, you're welcome at the inn.

Text.SourceString: Not that you would need it since you have your own house, but the offer is there.
Text.LocalizedString: Not that you would need it since you have your own house, but the offer is there.

Text.SourceString: Have you ever gone for a sunrise jog on the beach?//It clears your head.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you ever gone for a sunrise jog on the beach?//It clears your head.

Text.SourceString: I don’t want my head to be too clear, though. There are a lot of things I need to remember.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t want my head to be too clear, though. There are a lot of things I need to remember.

Text.SourceString: I run in the forest on Monday mornings… If the weather permits, that is.//<portrait=happy>I’ll hit the woodland tomorrow morning. I usually run back to the inn after taking <NPCName>Val</> to school.
Text.LocalizedString: I run in the forest on Monday mornings… If the weather permits, that is.//<portrait=happy>I’ll hit the woodland tomorrow morning. I usually run back to the inn after taking <NPCName>Val</> to school.

Text.SourceString: Yep, correct! <NPCName>Val</> is <NPCName>Valentina</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Yep, correct! <NPCName>Val</> is <NPCName>Valentina</>.

Text.SourceString: Deep breath in, deep breath out. Peace from within.
Text.LocalizedString: Deep breath in, deep breath out. Peace from within.

Text.SourceString: Okay, I’m good now. Do you need something, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Okay, I’m good now. Do you need something, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Don’t tell anyone, but I may have eaten one strawberry too many yesterday.//They’re so sweet! I’m not usually a big fan of strawberries, but I could eat some more, to be honest.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t tell anyone, but I may have eaten one strawberry too many yesterday.//They’re so sweet! I’m not usually a big fan of strawberries, but I could eat some more, to be honest.

Text.SourceString: Wait, were they from your farm?//<portrait=normal>I got them from <NPCName>Sam</>’s.
Text.LocalizedString: Wait, were they from your farm?//<portrait=normal>I got them from <NPCName>Sam</>’s.

Text.SourceString: I often see you walking past the inn. Been going to the diving spot, huh?//<portrait=happy>Good for you, <PlayerName>$player</>! I'm glad there are people like you who care not only about themselves but also about our environment.
Text.LocalizedString: I often see you walking past the inn. Been going to the diving spot, huh?//<portrait=happy>Good for you, <PlayerName>$player</>! I'm glad there are people like you who care not only about themselves but also about our environment.

Text.SourceString: Thank you, <PlayerName>$player</>. You’re very cool!
Text.LocalizedString: Thank you, <PlayerName>$player</>. You’re very cool!

Text.SourceString: I’m glad <NPCName>Valentina</> is close with <NPCName>Antonio’s</> family.//With her school being so small, I want to make sure she gets the social interaction she needs.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad <NPCName>Valentina</> is close with <NPCName>Antonio’s</> family.//With her school being so small, I want to make sure she gets the social interaction she needs.

Text.SourceString: I hope the more people <NPCName>Valentina</> is exposed to, the more she’ll learn about diversity, and the better her social skills will be.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope the more people <NPCName>Valentina</> is exposed to, the more she’ll learn about diversity, and the better her social skills will be.

Text.SourceString: The inn is open seven days a week. Gotta be there for the weekenders.
Text.LocalizedString: The inn is open seven days a week. Gotta be there for the weekenders.

Text.SourceString: There’s always so much cleaning to do at the inn.//I don’t mind, though. It keeps me moving.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s always so much cleaning to do at the inn.//I don’t mind, though. It keeps me moving.

Text.SourceString: I wish <NPCName>Alice</> would make more friends.//Spend less time reading up on those silly things she’s so interested in and actually live her life.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish <NPCName>Alice</> would make more friends.//Spend less time reading up on those silly things she’s so interested in and actually live her life.

Text.SourceString: Sorry, that was rude. Those things aren’t silly.//It’s just…<NPCName>Alice</> is too focused on them, and she doesn’t have any friends.//<portrait=concerned>Well, yeah. Valid point. <NPCName>Noah</> is her friend… But that’s the problem, isn’t it? <NPCName>Noah’s</> her <Italic>only</> friend.
Text.LocalizedString: Sorry, that was rude. Those things aren’t silly.//It’s just…<NPCName>Alice</> is too focused on them, and she doesn’t have any friends.//<portrait=concerned>Well, yeah. Valid point. <NPCName>Noah</> is her friend… But that’s the problem, isn’t it? <NPCName>Noah’s</> her <Italic>only</> friend.

Text.SourceString: My day’s been fantastic so far! Thanks for asking.//<portrait=normal><NPCName>Valentina</> just got her report card today. All As, as usual.
Text.LocalizedString: My day’s been fantastic so far! Thanks for asking.//<portrait=normal><NPCName>Valentina</> just got her report card today. All As, as usual.

Text.SourceString: Me? Nope. My grades were so-so. She must take after <NPCName>Antonio</>.//<portrait=happy>I was too busy having fun to focus on school.
Text.LocalizedString: Me? Nope. My grades were so-so. She must take after <NPCName>Antonio</>.//<portrait=happy>I was too busy having fun to focus on school.

Text.SourceString: Someone made a huge mess in one of the rooms at the inn a few days ago.//<portrait=concerned>It took me the whole day to clean up. Ugh, what a hassle.
Text.LocalizedString: Someone made a huge mess in one of the rooms at the inn a few days ago.//<portrait=concerned>It took me the whole day to clean up. Ugh, what a hassle.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Antonio</> had a fight last night. It rarely happens, so it bothers me when it does.//<portrait=concerned>He said I’m too naggy about <NPCName>Valentina</>.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Antonio</> had a fight last night. It rarely happens, so it bothers me when it does.//<portrait=concerned>He said I’m too naggy about <NPCName>Valentina</>.

Text.SourceString: Maybe <NPCName>Antonio</> has a point… But I just want the best for her.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe <NPCName>Antonio</> has a point… But I just want the best for her.

Text.SourceString: I wonder what <NPCName>Valentina</> will be when she grows up.//<portrait=normal>Whatever it is, I hope she finds her passion. Her dad and I will be right there, supporting her.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder what <NPCName>Valentina</> will be when she grows up.//<portrait=normal>Whatever it is, I hope she finds her passion. Her dad and I will be right there, supporting her.

Text.SourceString: The inn is ours…yeah. My parents used to run it before <NPCName>Alice</> and I took over.
Text.LocalizedString: The inn is ours…yeah. My parents used to run it before <NPCName>Alice</> and I took over.

Text.SourceString: You look surprised! Ha ha! Interesting reaction.
Text.LocalizedString: You look surprised! Ha ha! Interesting reaction.

Text.SourceString: Hmm… I can’t remember if I told <NPCName>Alice</> to clean out the inn’s reception desk or not.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… I can’t remember if I told <NPCName>Alice</> to clean out the inn’s reception desk or not.

Text.SourceString: I hope she does it anyway. It could use some tidying up.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope she does it anyway. It could use some tidying up.

Text.SourceString: Do you know of any good places to get exercise gear?//Wabanana is awesome, but if you have any other rad suggestions, I'm all ears.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you know of any good places to get exercise gear?//Wabanana is awesome, but if you have any other rad suggestions, I'm all ears.

Text.SourceString: Brooke, <NPCName>Charles’s</> ex, used to be my shopping buddy at Wabanana. We had a blast!
Text.LocalizedString: Brooke, <NPCName>Charles’s</> ex, used to be my shopping buddy at Wabanana. We had a blast!

Text.SourceString: It’s Friday! Got anything fun planned for the weekend?//<portrait=normal>I think I’m going to take it easy.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s Friday! Got anything fun planned for the weekend?//<portrait=normal>I think I’m going to take it easy.

Text.SourceString: Even though <NPCName>Antonio</> and I got divorced, I’m happy for the time we had together.//I have <NPCName>Valentina</> because of him, after all, and he’s taught me a lot about myself.
Text.LocalizedString: Even though <NPCName>Antonio</> and I got divorced, I’m happy for the time we had together.//I have <NPCName>Valentina</> because of him, after all, and he’s taught me a lot about myself.

Text.SourceString: Every once in a while, I think about <NPCName>Antonio’s</> parents. His mom made killer burritos.//<portrait=happy>I wonder how they’re doing.
Text.LocalizedString: Every once in a while, I think about <NPCName>Antonio’s</> parents. His mom made killer burritos.//<portrait=happy>I wonder how they’re doing.

Text.SourceString: I stepped on a rusty can during my jog this morning.//Thank goodness for my trusty, thick shoes. Crisis averted!
Text.LocalizedString: I stepped on a rusty can during my jog this morning.//Thank goodness for my trusty, thick shoes. Crisis averted!

Text.SourceString: I need to tell <NPCName>Valentina</> not to go barefoot on the beach.//<portrait=normal>Better safe than sorry.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to tell <NPCName>Valentina</> not to go barefoot on the beach.//<portrait=normal>Better safe than sorry.

Text.SourceString: It’s so nice having <NPCName>Rafael</> and <NPCName>Pablo</> around on Sundays.//They can keep an eye on <NPCName>Valentina</> while I run errands.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s so nice having <NPCName>Rafael</> and <NPCName>Pablo</> around on Sundays.//They can keep an eye on <NPCName>Valentina</> while I run errands.

Text.SourceString: I had a huge to-do list I wanted to get through yesterday, but I wasn’t able to finish everything.//Normally I’d be upset about it, but I feel…okay?
Text.LocalizedString: I had a huge to-do list I wanted to get through yesterday, but I wasn’t able to finish everything.//Normally I’d be upset about it, but I feel…okay?

Text.SourceString: I’ll just roll everything over to today. It’s not a big deal.//Wow, that feels weird to say…but in a good way.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll just roll everything over to today. It’s not a big deal.//Wow, that feels weird to say…but in a good way.

Text.SourceString: Woo-hoo! It's that time of year again—Spring cleaning extravaganza!//Out with the old, in with the fabulously fresh!
Text.LocalizedString: Woo-hoo! It's that time of year again—Spring cleaning extravaganza!//Out with the old, in with the fabulously fresh!

Text.SourceString: Spring is the perfect time to start new habits.//Everyone’s shaking off the Winter cold and getting outside again.
Text.LocalizedString: Spring is the perfect time to start new habits.//Everyone’s shaking off the Winter cold and getting outside again.

Text.SourceString: What sort of flowers should I plant around the inn this year?//I’ll have to check my plant notebook for ideas.
Text.LocalizedString: What sort of flowers should I plant around the inn this year?//I’ll have to check my plant notebook for ideas.

Text.SourceString: I’ll plant anything but violets.//<portrait=annoyed>I just hate the way they smell.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll plant anything but violets.//<portrait=annoyed>I just hate the way they smell.

Text.SourceString: Summer is a good time to burn away bad vibes.//Just lie back on the beach and let the sun do its thing.//Don’t forget sunscreen, though!
Text.LocalizedString: Summer is a good time to burn away bad vibes.//Just lie back on the beach and let the sun do its thing.//Don’t forget sunscreen, though!

Text.SourceString: I need to keep an eye on how much candy <NPCName>Valentina</> eats.//She’ll make herself sick otherwise.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to keep an eye on how much candy <NPCName>Valentina</> eats.//She’ll make herself sick otherwise.

Text.SourceString: I can’t believe it’s time for <NPCName>Valentina</> to start another year of school. She’s growing up way too fast.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t believe it’s time for <NPCName>Valentina</> to start another year of school. She’s growing up way too fast.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Antonio</> and I used to spend Fall going to concerts and music festivals. I can’t really see myself doing that anymore.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Antonio</> and I used to spend Fall going to concerts and music festivals. I can’t really see myself doing that anymore.

Text.SourceString: There’s so much fresh food to cook with in Fall. It makes planning <NPCName>Valentina’s</> meals much easier.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s so much fresh food to cook with in Fall. It makes planning <NPCName>Valentina’s</> meals much easier.

Text.SourceString: She <Italic>loves</> red curry but can’t eat mushrooms.//Poor thing.
Text.LocalizedString: She <Italic>loves</> red curry but can’t eat mushrooms.//Poor thing.

Text.SourceString: Have you made your plans for Winter yet, <PlayerName>$player</>?//Now’s the time to get started.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you made your plans for Winter yet, <PlayerName>$player</>?//Now’s the time to get started.

Text.SourceString: We don’t get many customers at the inn in Winter.//I think people prefer to stay in their own houses during the cold months.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t know. What do you think?
Text.LocalizedString: We don’t get many customers at the inn in Winter.//I think people prefer to stay in their own houses during the cold months.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t know. What do you think?

Text.SourceString: I grew up here, and I’m still having a hard time adjusting to this weather.
Text.LocalizedString: I grew up here, and I’m still having a hard time adjusting to this weather.

Text.SourceString: I hope it doesn’t snow on my birthday.//I’d like to go on a jog without getting my shoes wet.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope it doesn’t snow on my birthday.//I’d like to go on a jog without getting my shoes wet.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Rafael</> and <NPCName>Pablo</> bring <NPCName>Valentina</> too many gifts this time of year.//They’re going to spoil her!
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Rafael</> and <NPCName>Pablo</> bring <NPCName>Valentina</> too many gifts this time of year.//They’re going to spoil her!

Text.SourceString: I’ve heard rain is 40 percent more dangerous at night than during the day.//I don’t think <NPCName>Valentina</> will be going out by herself on rainy nights anymore.//<portrait=normal>Ha ha! That’s right. I do like statistics.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve heard rain is 40 percent more dangerous at night than during the day.//I don’t think <NPCName>Valentina</> will be going out by herself on rainy nights anymore.//<portrait=normal>Ha ha! That’s right. I do like statistics.

Text.SourceString: I’ve heard rain is 40 percent more dangerous at night than during the day.//I don’t think <NPCName>Valentina</> will be going out by herself on rainy nights anymore.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve heard rain is 40 percent more dangerous at night than during the day.//I don’t think <NPCName>Valentina</> will be going out by herself on rainy nights anymore.

Text.SourceString: Oh my! Really? Ha ha! I never noticed.//<portrait=normal>You’re right. I do like statistics.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh my! Really? Ha ha! I never noticed.//<portrait=normal>You’re right. I do like statistics.

Text.SourceString: What a gloomy day. Thank goodness I'm chilling indoors.
Text.LocalizedString: What a gloomy day. Thank goodness I'm chilling indoors.

Text.SourceString: Didn’t the weather forecast say it wasn’t going to rain today?
Text.LocalizedString: Didn’t the weather forecast say it wasn’t going to rain today?

Text.SourceString: I thought I’d be able to take <NPCName>Valentina</> to the beach this evening, but I guess not.
Text.LocalizedString: I thought I’d be able to take <NPCName>Valentina</> to the beach this evening, but I guess not.

Text.SourceString: I hope this clears up by tomorrow morning.//I’d rather not take <NPCName>Valentina</> to school in the rain.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope this clears up by tomorrow morning.//I’d rather not take <NPCName>Valentina</> to school in the rain.

Text.SourceString: This is dangerous weather, <PlayerName>$player</>! Neither of us should be out in it!
Text.LocalizedString: This is dangerous weather, <PlayerName>$player</>! Neither of us should be out in it!

Text.SourceString: Either way, I still have to get my to-do list done! Please excuse me.
Text.LocalizedString: Either way, I still have to get my to-do list done! Please excuse me.

Text.SourceString: I hope a branch doesn’t fall on the inn.//That would be expensive.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope a branch doesn’t fall on the inn.//That would be expensive.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Valentina</> hates thunder.//I should make sure she’s okay.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Valentina</> hates thunder.//I should make sure she’s okay.

Text.SourceString: I hope we don’t lose power.//One time, there was a really bad storm, and the electricity was out for the whole day.//<portrait=normal>Yeah! A blackout.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope we don’t lose power.//One time, there was a really bad storm, and the electricity was out for the whole day.//<portrait=normal>Yeah! A blackout.

Text.SourceString: It’s part of living on an island, I guess.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s part of living on an island, I guess.

Text.SourceString: Be careful on your way home. You don’t want to be struck by lightning or anything.
Text.LocalizedString: Be careful on your way home. You don’t want to be struck by lightning or anything.

Text.SourceString: Even though I don’t like Winter, the snow does make the inn look pretty.//It makes the whole town look pretty, actually.
Text.LocalizedString: Even though I don’t like Winter, the snow does make the inn look pretty.//It makes the whole town look pretty, actually.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Valentina’s</> hoping for a day off from school tomorrow.//If it keeps snowing like this, she might get it.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Valentina’s</> hoping for a day off from school tomorrow.//If it keeps snowing like this, she might get it.

Text.SourceString: I wish I could stay and talk, but I need to find some extra blankets for <NPCName>Valentina’s</> bed.//It’s going to be a chilly night.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish I could stay and talk, but I need to find some extra blankets for <NPCName>Valentina’s</> bed.//It’s going to be a chilly night.

Text.SourceString: Now, where did I put that grocery list?//I can’t remember if it’s in the budget notebook, the food notebook, or the shopping notebook. Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: Now, where did I put that grocery list?//I can’t remember if it’s in the budget notebook, the food notebook, or the shopping notebook. Hmm…

Text.SourceString: If you see <NPCName>Valentina</>, could you send her over here, please?//I want to show her something.
Text.LocalizedString: If you see <NPCName>Valentina</>, could you send her over here, please?//I want to show her something.

Text.SourceString: Teaching her how to keep the inn’s ledger will help with her math skills.
Text.LocalizedString: Teaching her how to keep the inn’s ledger will help with her math skills.

Text.SourceString: Ugh! <NPCName>Alice</> messed up the numbers again.//<portrait=annoyed>I had everything all neat and organized in my spreadsheet, and now it's a total mess.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh! <NPCName>Alice</> messed up the numbers again.//<portrait=annoyed>I had everything all neat and organized in my spreadsheet, and now it's a total mess.

Text.SourceString: This is going to take ages to fix.
Text.LocalizedString: This is going to take ages to fix.

Text.SourceString: What’s still on my to-do list? Oh, right.//I need to make <NPCName>Valentina’s</> lunch for tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: What’s still on my to-do list? Oh, right.//I need to make <NPCName>Valentina’s</> lunch for tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: Would you do me a favor and check the expiration date on the ketchup?//I think it’s going bad.
Text.LocalizedString: Would you do me a favor and check the expiration date on the ketchup?//I think it’s going bad.

Text.SourceString: I tried some earlier, and it tasted kinda funky.
Text.LocalizedString: I tried some earlier, and it tasted kinda funky.

Text.SourceString: I’m sorry, but I don’t feel like chatting… I’m a little tired.//<portrait=normal>Let’s talk later?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m sorry, but I don’t feel like chatting… I’m a little tired.//<portrait=normal>Let’s talk later?

Text.SourceString: *humming*
Text.LocalizedString: *humming*

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I bring <NPCName>Valentina</> here to calm down when she’s upset.//The peace and quiet among the trees helps her.//<portrait=happy>It helps me too.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I bring <NPCName>Valentina</> here to calm down when she’s upset.//The peace and quiet among the trees helps her.//<portrait=happy>It helps me too.

Text.SourceString: I should get <NPCName>Rafael</> and <NPCName>Pablo</> to teach <NPCName>Valentina</> about farm animals.//Maybe she can help out at the ranch when she’s a little older.
Text.LocalizedString: I should get <NPCName>Rafael</> and <NPCName>Pablo</> to teach <NPCName>Valentina</> about farm animals.//Maybe she can help out at the ranch when she’s a little older.

Text.SourceString: I hope <NPCName>Sam</> stocks more fresh vegetables soon.//I’m running out of ingredients for green smoothies.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope <NPCName>Sam</> stocks more fresh vegetables soon.//I’m running out of ingredients for green smoothies.

Text.SourceString: I have nothing against sweet things.//I just don’t really enjoy them, I guess.
Text.LocalizedString: I have nothing against sweet things.//I just don’t really enjoy them, I guess.

Text.SourceString: Cakes, pizza… They’re so heavy. I usually get really bloated the next day.//<portrait=happy>Sorry if that was too much information. Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: Cakes, pizza… They’re so heavy. I usually get really bloated the next day.//<portrait=happy>Sorry if that was too much information. Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: I brought my own bag, right here! You too, right?//<portrait=happy>Awesome!
Text.LocalizedString: I brought my own bag, right here! You too, right?//<portrait=happy>Awesome!

Text.SourceString: I miss school sometimes. It was nice having a clear path ahead, one grade after another.
Text.LocalizedString: I miss school sometimes. It was nice having a clear path ahead, one grade after another.

Text.SourceString: But being an adult is a whole different ballgame.//<portrait=normal>Still feel like a kid at times, even though I've got this little human relying on me. Life's full of surprises, that's for sure.
Text.LocalizedString: But being an adult is a whole different ballgame.//<portrait=normal>Still feel like a kid at times, even though I've got this little human relying on me. Life's full of surprises, that's for sure.

Text.SourceString: [<NPCName>Suki</> is concentrating on her putt.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NPCName>Suki</> is concentrating on her putt.]

Text.SourceString: I can’t believe I missed that putt! I need to calculate my angle better next time.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t believe I missed that putt! I need to calculate my angle better next time.

Text.SourceString: So, if I hit it at a forty-five degree angle off this wall…
Text.LocalizedString: So, if I hit it at a forty-five degree angle off this wall…

Text.SourceString: Oh, hey! I’m glad you’re here.//<portrait=normal>Wanna help me sweep? Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, hey! I’m glad you’re here.//<portrait=normal>Wanna help me sweep? Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: Sorry, I can’t hang out now. I’m in the middle of cleaning up.
Text.LocalizedString: Sorry, I can’t hang out now. I’m in the middle of cleaning up.

Text.SourceString: Diving? No, thank you. I think I’ll just stay here with my broom…on solid ground.//You should go, though!
Text.LocalizedString: Diving? No, thank you. I think I’ll just stay here with my broom…on solid ground.//You should go, though!

Text.SourceString: Diamonds and pearls always bring back such happy memories.
Text.LocalizedString: Diamonds and pearls always bring back such happy memories.

Text.SourceString: They're just so personal and special to me. Definitely my favorite things.
Text.LocalizedString: They're just so personal and special to me. Definitely my favorite things.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Valentina’s</> at the age when I can’t tell if she’s being serious or if she’s teasing me with her ideas.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Valentina’s</> at the age when I can’t tell if she’s being serious or if she’s teasing me with her ideas.

Text.SourceString: I’m usually on desk duty all day on the weekends. Humph… Boring.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m usually on desk duty all day on the weekends. Humph… Boring.

Text.SourceString: But it gives me some time to sit down.//<portrait=happy>I’ve been running around town all week long. Gotta stop sometimes, right?
Text.LocalizedString: But it gives me some time to sit down.//<portrait=happy>I’ve been running around town all week long. Gotta stop sometimes, right?

Text.SourceString: There’s a yoga class tomorrow in the community center. A lot of people usually turn up.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s a yoga class tomorrow in the community center. A lot of people usually turn up.

Text.SourceString: I think my sister’s also in the class… Um… I don’t really know for sure.
Text.LocalizedString: I think my sister’s also in the class… Um… I don’t really know for sure.

Text.SourceString: Working hard, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Working hard, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Did you check out the yoga class yesterday? Was it fun?
Text.LocalizedString: Did you check out the yoga class yesterday? Was it fun?

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Alice</> said she saw you in town yesterday.//So I thought…you know… Anyway.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Alice</> said she saw you in town yesterday.//So I thought…you know… Anyway.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Nina</> left town when she was really young, right after her dad passed away.//<portrait=concerned>I guess it was just too much for her and her mom, living in a place filled with memories.//I get it...
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Nina</> left town when she was really young, right after her dad passed away.//<portrait=concerned>I guess it was just too much for her and her mom, living in a place filled with memories.//I get it...

Text.SourceString: That year was tough on her, losing her dad and having to start fresh in a new place.
Text.LocalizedString: That year was tough on her, losing her dad and having to start fresh in a new place.

Text.SourceString: When I told <NpcName>Antonio</> I wanted to move back to Starlet Town, we went back and forth about where <NpcName>Valentina</> would live.
Text.LocalizedString: When I told <NpcName>Antonio</> I wanted to move back to Starlet Town, we went back and forth about where <NpcName>Valentina</> would live.

Text.SourceString: Since <NpcName>Antonio</> travels a lot for his business, we decided she’d come with me.//<portrait=sad>It wasn’t an easy decision, but I think it’s the right one.
Text.LocalizedString: Since <NpcName>Antonio</> travels a lot for his business, we decided she’d come with me.//<portrait=sad>It wasn’t an easy decision, but I think it’s the right one.

Text.SourceString: Can I ask you something? You can tell me and <NpcName>Alice</> apart, right?
Text.LocalizedString: Can I ask you something? You can tell me and <NpcName>Alice</> apart, right?

Text.SourceString: Cause if you can't, we might be in some trouble!
Text.LocalizedString: Cause if you can't, we might be in some trouble!

Text.SourceString: They say around 50 percent of marriages end in divorce, so statistically speaking, it's not too surprising that <NpcName>Antonio</> and I separated.
Text.LocalizedString: They say around 50 percent of marriages end in divorce, so statistically speaking, it's not too surprising that <NpcName>Antonio</> and I separated.

Text.SourceString: I did love him, and to some extent, I still do...just not in a romantic way.//We're great friends.
Text.LocalizedString: I did love him, and to some extent, I still do...just not in a romantic way.//We're great friends.

Text.SourceString: You know what the hardest part of co-parenting is?//Somehow, <NpcName>Antonio</> became the fun parent, and I’m the strict one! Me!
Text.LocalizedString: You know what the hardest part of co-parenting is?//Somehow, <NpcName>Antonio</> became the fun parent, and I’m the strict one! Me!

Text.SourceString: Wait until <NpcName>Valentina</> hears about my college days. Or maybe I shouldn’t tell her…
Text.LocalizedString: Wait until <NpcName>Valentina</> hears about my college days. Or maybe I shouldn’t tell her…

Text.SourceString: I know <NpcName>Valentina</> hates the healthy food I feed her, but she’s going to thank me one day!
Text.LocalizedString: I know <NpcName>Valentina</> hates the healthy food I feed her, but she’s going to thank me one day!

Text.SourceString: Ugh, I’m turning into my mom.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh, I’m turning into my mom.

Text.SourceString: Ah, I might go mini golfing on Wednesday.//<portrait=normal>Hopefully, <NpcName>Ben’s</> in town… He’s a great opponent.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, I might go mini golfing on Wednesday.//<portrait=normal>Hopefully, <NpcName>Ben’s</> in town… He’s a great opponent.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Alice</> takes care of the inn in the morning. Then I take over for the evening shift.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Alice</> takes care of the inn in the morning. Then I take over for the evening shift.

Text.SourceString: My shift starts around five-ish. I need to see how the inn is doing, supply-wise, to prepare for tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: My shift starts around five-ish. I need to see how the inn is doing, supply-wise, to prepare for tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: Let me tell you something… I’ve been wearing my hair purple for as long as I can remember.//If I didn’t keep my roots natural, I probably would have forgotten my real hair color.
Text.LocalizedString: Let me tell you something… I’ve been wearing my hair purple for as long as I can remember.//If I didn’t keep my roots natural, I probably would have forgotten my real hair color.

Text.SourceString: Do you wear a hat when you farm?//The sun is in full force.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you wear a hat when you farm?//The sun is in full force.

Text.SourceString: Don’t overheat, <PlayerName>$Player</>. That would not be good.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t overheat, <PlayerName>$Player</>. That would not be good.

Text.SourceString: My sister and I may look a bit alike, but we have a different approach to things.
Text.LocalizedString: My sister and I may look a bit alike, but we have a different approach to things.

Text.SourceString: I always used to get us in trouble, growing up. *laughs* <NpcName>Alice</>, she’s very…um…<Italic>tamed</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I always used to get us in trouble, growing up. *laughs* <NpcName>Alice</>, she’s very…um…<Italic>tamed</>.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know how to say this without sounding like… Errr… *sighs*
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know how to say this without sounding like… Errr… *sighs*

Text.SourceString: I’m worried… I worry about <NpcName>Alice</> all the time.//She’s too soft sometimes. I’m afraid someone might see it as an opportunity and take advantage of her good heart.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m worried… I worry about <NpcName>Alice</> all the time.//She’s too soft sometimes. I’m afraid someone might see it as an opportunity and take advantage of her good heart.

Text.SourceString: I hope Pufferfish stops drilling.//Not just here, but I hope they change their business direction altogether.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope Pufferfish stops drilling.//Not just here, but I hope they change their business direction altogether.

Text.SourceString: Far-fetched, I know…
Text.LocalizedString: Far-fetched, I know…

Text.SourceString: You should’ve seen <NpcName>Alice</> and me at university.
Text.LocalizedString: You should’ve seen <NpcName>Alice</> and me at university.

Text.SourceString: Or even in grade school. She would just sit under a tree by herself or stay in her room all weekend, doing nothing.
Text.LocalizedString: Or even in grade school. She would just sit under a tree by herself or stay in her room all weekend, doing nothing.

Text.SourceString: I literally had to drag her out of her dorm so she’d at least have some friends… Good gosh.
Text.LocalizedString: I literally had to drag her out of her dorm so she’d at least have some friends… Good gosh.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Antonio</> and I separated as nicely as possible. Nothing dramatic happened, no cheating or anything like that.//We simply realized we didn't fit together anymore. We were young when we tied the knot, and we've grown into different individuals.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Antonio</> and I separated as nicely as possible. Nothing dramatic happened, no cheating or anything like that.//We simply realized we didn't fit together anymore. We were young when we tied the knot, and we've grown into different individuals.

Text.SourceString: He is a fantastic dad despite my occasional complaints. He loves <NpcName>Valentina</> and me…//<portrait=happy>And to tell you the truth, the feeling is mutual. I'll always have love for him, just not in a romantic way.
Text.LocalizedString: He is a fantastic dad despite my occasional complaints. He loves <NpcName>Valentina</> and me…//<portrait=happy>And to tell you the truth, the feeling is mutual. I'll always have love for him, just not in a romantic way.

Text.SourceString: Well, I don't really care if I hurt anyone's feelings.//If I see my sister heading down a rough path in a relationship, I'll definitely speak up.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, I don't really care if I hurt anyone's feelings.//If I see my sister heading down a rough path in a relationship, I'll definitely speak up.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Alice</> is such a sensitive soul.//She accepts everything, and the problem is, I don't want her to.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Alice</> is such a sensitive soul.//She accepts everything, and the problem is, I don't want her to.

Text.SourceString: Look, <PlayerName>$player</>. We’re friends now, so I feel like I can tell you stuff.//<portrait=sad>I’m torn, you know… I love my sister, I do.
Text.LocalizedString: Look, <PlayerName>$player</>. We’re friends now, so I feel like I can tell you stuff.//<portrait=sad>I’m torn, you know… I love my sister, I do.

Text.SourceString: But I honestly can’t trust anyone to keep her feelings safe.//<portrait=sad>Back in university, when she had her first breakup, she was an absolute mess.//That's where my worries stem from.
Text.LocalizedString: But I honestly can’t trust anyone to keep her feelings safe.//<portrait=sad>Back in university, when she had her first breakup, she was an absolute mess.//That's where my worries stem from.

Text.SourceString: My sister asked me about my dating plans...and I told her that I'm looking for a partner, not another parent for<NpcName>Valentina</>.
Text.LocalizedString: My sister asked me about my dating plans...and I told her that I'm looking for a partner, not another parent for<NpcName>Valentina</>.

Text.SourceString: But that doesn't mean a potential partner would only deal with me.//<portrait=happy><NpcName>Valentina</> and I are a package deal. I'm her mom forever, and <NpcName>Antonio</> will always be her dad.
Text.LocalizedString: But that doesn't mean a potential partner would only deal with me.//<portrait=happy><NpcName>Valentina</> and I are a package deal. I'm her mom forever, and <NpcName>Antonio</> will always be her dad.

Text.SourceString: Dating as a single parent is hard. I have to make sure they get along with my daughter.
Text.LocalizedString: Dating as a single parent is hard. I have to make sure they get along with my daughter.

Text.SourceString: And let’s not forget about her father.//My ex is gonna be in my life <Italic>period</>, so it would be nice if they get along with him as well.
Text.LocalizedString: And let’s not forget about her father.//My ex is gonna be in my life <Italic>period</>, so it would be nice if they get along with him as well.

Text.SourceString: Not that I need his permission! Nothing like that.//<portrait=normal>But if <NpcName>Antonio</> likes whoever I’m dating, it makes life easier.
Text.LocalizedString: Not that I need his permission! Nothing like that.//<portrait=normal>But if <NpcName>Antonio</> likes whoever I’m dating, it makes life easier.

Text.SourceString: I thought I’d have to wait until <NpcName>Valentina</> was a teenager or even an adult before I could start dating again.
Text.LocalizedString: I thought I’d have to wait until <NpcName>Valentina</> was a teenager or even an adult before I could start dating again.

Text.SourceString: It turned out that I didn't have to wait that long.
Text.LocalizedString: It turned out that I didn't have to wait that long.

Text.SourceString: I hope you’re not intimidated by <NpcName>Antonio</>. He’s just a bit protective when it comes to me and <NpcName>Valentina</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope you’re not intimidated by <NpcName>Antonio</>. He’s just a bit protective when it comes to me and <NpcName>Valentina</>.

Text.SourceString: You’re very responsible with your farm
Text.LocalizedString: You’re very responsible with your farm

Text.SourceString: I like that. It shows how dependable you are.
Text.LocalizedString: I like that. It shows how dependable you are.

Text.SourceString: Oh, hey, you! What a nice surprise.//<portrait=blushing>You look amazing today. Wow! I don’t know what to say.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, hey, you! What a nice surprise.//<portrait=blushing>You look amazing today. Wow! I don’t know what to say.

Text.SourceString: It’s foolish of me to think my divorce won’t affect <NpcName>Valentina</> at all…//But I’m trying to do my best here.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s foolish of me to think my divorce won’t affect <NpcName>Valentina</> at all…//But I’m trying to do my best here.

Text.SourceString: I hope <NpcName>Valentina</> doesn’t miss out on anything.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope <NpcName>Valentina</> doesn’t miss out on anything.

Text.SourceString: The inn can get pretty messy sometimes because <NpcName>Macy</> keeps a lobster in her room...yeah!
Text.LocalizedString: The inn can get pretty messy sometimes because <NpcName>Macy</> keeps a lobster in her room...yeah!

Text.SourceString: She's nursing it back to health, so we're supportive of her kind heart.
Text.LocalizedString: She's nursing it back to health, so we're supportive of her kind heart.

Text.SourceString: To be fair… Look, I know I can be too much to handle as a sister.//<portrait=sad>I know I can seem pushy, but I have no ill will in my heart. I just want to protect my sister…//<portrait=concerned>I understand it’s not okay. I’m learning to be more respectful.
Text.LocalizedString: To be fair… Look, I know I can be too much to handle as a sister.//<portrait=sad>I know I can seem pushy, but I have no ill will in my heart. I just want to protect my sister…//<portrait=concerned>I understand it’s not okay. I’m learning to be more respectful.

Text.SourceString: I’m trying to back off a bit… Errr…trying to give her some space.//But I’ll never leave her side, and she knows I’ll always have her back.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m trying to back off a bit… Errr…trying to give her some space.//But I’ll never leave her side, and she knows I’ll always have her back.

Text.SourceString: I can’t help but smile every time I see you smile.//It’s contagious.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t help but smile every time I see you smile.//It’s contagious.

Text.SourceString: Is that a new outfit? It suits you.//You look good, <PlayerName>$Player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Is that a new outfit? It suits you.//You look good, <PlayerName>$Player</>.

Text.SourceString: Oh gosh, you’re making me blush.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh gosh, you’re making me blush.

Text.SourceString: You’re a great friend, <PlayerName>$player</>. It’s always nice to hear fresh perspectives on things.//<portrait=happy>Thank you for being a great listener.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re a great friend, <PlayerName>$player</>. It’s always nice to hear fresh perspectives on things.//<portrait=happy>Thank you for being a great listener.

Text.SourceString: Oh, my hair? Aww! Thank you! Yes, I just got my hair done a couple of days ago.//<portrait=happy><NPCName>Erika</> did a fantastic job, I thought.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, my hair? Aww! Thank you! Yes, I just got my hair done a couple of days ago.//<portrait=happy><NPCName>Erika</> did a fantastic job, I thought.

Text.SourceString: She’s also having me use this new shampoo…Prestesse?//<portrait=annoyed>It was very pricey, but apparently it holds color better. Let’s see how it goes!
Text.LocalizedString: She’s also having me use this new shampoo…Prestesse?//<portrait=annoyed>It was very pricey, but apparently it holds color better. Let’s see how it goes!
